      "contents": "<div class=\"markitup-box aw-briefly\">\n\t\t\thttps://www.goodreads.com/book/show/63068790-seventeen<br/>\n<br/>\n<blockquote>For his final two years at school, he is bound to her, a woman twice his age, in an <b>increasingly tangled web of coercion, sex and lies. Their affair, a product of complex grooming and a shocking abuse of authority</b>, is played out in the corridors of one of Britain’s major private schools, under the noses of people who suspected, even knew, but said nothing. <br/>\n<br/>\nThirty years on, this is Joe’s gripping record of the illicit relationship that dominated his adolescence and dictated the course of his life. With a heady dose of nineties nostalgia and the perfectly captured mood of those final months at school, Joe charts the enduring legacy of deceit and the indelibility of decisions made at seventeen. </blockquote><br/>\n<br/>\nhttps://duckduckgo.com/?q=school+teacher+minor+sex&amp;ia=web<br/>\n<br/>\n这应该是个涉及到未成年人的刑事案件，特别是换成男老师和女学生就不难理解，<br/>\n<br/>\n英国有大量这种刑事案件的案例，要坐牢的，<br/>\n<br/>\nhttps://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-glasgow-west-60954157<br/>\nhttps://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-berkshire-61230140<br/>\nhttps://www.bbc.com/news/newsbeat-25367715\t\t<div class=\"aw-stretch-content-button-container\"><button class=\"aw-stretch-content-button\" type=\"button\"></button></div></div>",
